<br>
Perhaps, but a bunch of untrained joe-blows are the <i>worst</i> people to have deciding something like punitive damages.  Punitive damages have nothing to do with deciding who's telling the truth or what really happened.  If McDonald's should be punished (and I'm not necessarily saying they should), the person deciding the punishment should be someone intimately familiar with the industry, economics, and the broader ramifications of such awards in the aggregate.  You wouldn't hire joe blow to chair the Federal Reserve Bank or to take over as CEO of a major company, and this is no different.  Also, there is no reason on earth why the plaintiff, or her attorney, should get one cent of that money.<br>
<br>
In brief, the system is royally fücked up.  <img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/biggrin.txt> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaurincotg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saurin CoTG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/13/02 10:05:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BSI suing Mythic RE:IRL Auctions - Enjoy Scirocco</span><hr size=1> Tudamorf stated:<br>
