Not True.  I'm not selling the little data bits off of Mythic's computers.  I'm selling my access rights to those bits.   The rights to those bits are awarded to me via access fees.  <br>
<br>
I really don't see what the big deal is.  I don't buy or sell anything on Ebay, but frankly, who gives a rats ass anyway.   If I had never once heard of Ebay and unless someone told me, I could spend 10 years in DAoC, EQ, AC, etc and still not be able to objectively quantify how exactly it is that Ebay affects my character.   No one can, they conjecture, theorize and claim it's bad, it causes camping, it does this it does that.  They can't prove it causes anything, no one can. I think Ebay is just a nice friendly scapegoat to lump all the ills of the world upon.<br>
<br>
What some people fail to realize is that demand will always exceed supply.   When supply exceeds demand, demand disappears.  This means that coveted items will ALWAYS be camped if they are campable.  ALWAYS.   Ending Ebay won't end trading of items or characters, there will always be a medium of exchange.<br>
<br>
The argument 'well, they don't deserve it, I did it legitimately and camped  the frenzied for 36 hours straight myself' doesn't hold much water either.   It comes down to people comparing themselves to others constantly.  I can't stand in town in AC for more than 5 minutes without at least one person examining me.    People seem to want to &quot;be better than the other guy&quot;.   Frankly though, someone else having the ultimate sword of whoop-ass doesn't detract from my accomplishment of beating Bael Zha'ron naked in the slightest.   The moment I'm more concerned about what someone else has or  how they got it, is the moment I've given over my locus of control to others, why on Earth/Norrath/Dereth/Etc would anyone do that?   *shakes head*<br>
<br>
I've never figured out why people care.   Try this experiment.  Make a character in whatever game, talk to the fewest people possible and level them from 1 to 50/60/126 and make no mention of Ebay or trading or whatever.  When done come back here and quantitatively state how it was that Ebay affected your game?   Bet you won't be able to state one example of where it affected you.  Oh and anecdotal 'We went to the hand and it was camped, so it must be Ebay' doesn't work.<br>
<br>
I'm waiting...<br>
<br>
-Mal<br>
<br>
